class Solution(object):
    def beautifulSubstrings(self, s, k):
        """
        :type s: str
        :type k: int
        :rtype: int
        """
        vowels = "aeiou"
        n = len(s)
        count = 0
        
        # Precompute vowel and consonant counts for all substrings
        prefix_vowels = [0] * (n + 1)
        prefix_consonants = [0] * (n + 1)
        
        for i in range(n):
            prefix_vowels[i + 1] = prefix_vowels[i] + (s[i] in vowels)
            prefix_consonants[i + 1] = prefix_consonants[i] + (s[i] not in vowels)
        
        for i in range(n):
            for j in range(i + 1, n + 1):
                v = prefix_vowels[j] - prefix_vowels[i]
                c = prefix_consonants[j] - prefix_consonants[i]
                if v == c and (v * c) % k == 0:
                    count += 1
        
        return count
